---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import { getRelativeLocaleUrl } from 'astro:i18n';

const lang = Astro.currentLocale || 'en';
---

<Layout title="About the project | 100cosas.dev">
	<Navbar alternateUrl="/sobre-el-proyecto" />
	
	<main class="flex-grow max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20 w-full">
		<header class="mb-12">
			<h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white mb-6 tracking-tight">
				About the <span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-sky-400 to-blue-500">project</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="text-xl text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
				An initiative by <a href="https://midu.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-sky-400 hover:underline">midudev</a> to strengthen the foundations of software development.
			</p>
		</header>

		<div class="prose prose-invert prose-sky max-w-none space-y-8 text-slate-300">
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
					<span class="text-sky-500">#</span> Why this project?
				</h2>
				<p>
					This project was born out of the need to collect and modernize fundamental advice for programmers. It is inspired by the collective work <strong>"97 Things Every Programmer Should Know"</strong>, adapting its content to an interactive and accessible format.
				</p>
				<p>
					The goal is to offer a roadmap of knowledge that transcends specific programming languages and frameworks.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
					<span class="text-sky-500">#</span> What does it provide?
				</h2>
				<p>
					100cosas.dev is not just a list of advice; it is a tool to:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
					<li><strong>Reflect</strong> on the daily practice of programming.</li>
					<li><strong>Discover</strong> design and architecture principles that are often overlooked.</li>
					<li><strong>Keep a record</strong> of your learning, marking the concepts you already master.</li>
					<li><strong>Multi-language support</strong>: Now available in both Spanish and English.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="bg-slate-800/50 border border-slate-700 rounded-2xl p-8 mt-12">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
					<span class="text-sky-500">#</span> Programming in the AI era
				</h2>
				<p class="mb-4">
					We live in an era where Artificial Intelligence can generate code in seconds. However, this makes <strong>having solid foundations more important than ever</strong>.
				</p>
				<p class="mb-4 text-slate-200 font-medium">
					Why? Because AI is a tool, not a substitute for professional judgment.
				</p>
				<p>
					Understanding the "why" behind the code, knowing when a solution is scalable, detecting code smells, and applying robust design principles is what allows a programmer to guide the AI, rather than being guided by it. <strong>Foundations are the basis that allow you to discern if what the AI generates is really the best solution for your problem.</strong>
				</p>
			</section>
		</div>

		<div class="mt-16 flex justify-center">
			<a href={getRelativeLocaleUrl(lang, "/")} class="px-8 py-3 bg-slate-800 hover:bg-slate-700 text-white rounded-xl font-bold transition-all border border-slate-700">
				Back to home
			</a>
		</div>
	</main>

	<Footer />
</Layout>
